main event: A UFO was observed over the Gulf of Mexico between Cortez and Bradenton, Florida on January 27, 1949.
interesting points: The object was described as cucumber-shaped, emitted light from six windows, and was observed to travel at speeds of approximately 400 mph., The object was seen climbing and descending erratically, losing altitude and then disappearing from view at around 40,000 feet., It was observed using binoculars from a moving vehicle, with a clear view for about 25 to 30 minutes., The observer noted that the sparks emitted from the object were brighter than a V-1 exhaust trail., The report includes a description of the observer as serious and disturbed by the incident, indicating credibility.
sighted object: one cucumber-shaped object with lighted windows
witness description: Capt. Scoreran Sannes, USAF and his wife Dorothy
